description: Rails 8 Controller Rules
globs:
  - "app/controllers/**/*.rb"
alwaysApply: false
---

# Controllers

- Always inherit from ApplicationController (which inherits from ActionController::API)
- Always use strong parameters — never use params directly
- Always rescue_from in ApplicationController for common errors:
  ActiveRecord::RecordNotFound → 404
  ActiveRecord::RecordInvalid → 422
  ActionController::ParameterMissing → 400
- Namespace all API controllers under Api::V1
- File path: app/controllers/api/v1/farms_controller.rb
- Class name: Api::V1::FarmsController
- Always use before_action for authentication
- Always use before_action :set_resource for finding records
- Return consistent JSON envelope: { data:, meta:, errors: }
- Use render json: with explicit status codes
- Never rescue specific errors in individual controllers — use ApplicationController
- **Exception:** AI endpoints `include RescuesAi` (`rails_helpers.mdc`) for `Ai::ConfigurationError` / `Ai::ApiError`
- Async resources: return `202 Accepted` when enqueueing jobs (e.g. `POST .../report` → `GenerateAnalystReportJob`)